  <data name="ManualSect4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>4. CLIPBOARD AND CONTEXT MENU</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect4_1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Copying:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect4_2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Select bytes and press Ctrl+C or right-click -&gt; 'Copy'. Data is exported to the Windows clipboard as a HEX string (e.g., '41 00 FF').</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect4_3.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Smart Paste:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect4_4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Press Ctrl+V or right-click -&gt; 'Paste'. The program will grab the HEX text from the clipboard, automatically strip whitespaces/hyphens, parse it into a byte array, and overwrite the file starting from the cursor position.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect5.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>5. GLOBAL SEARCH AND NAVIGATION</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect5_1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Automated Signature Search:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect5_2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Press Ctrl+F or go to 'View -&gt; Search File'. Type your query. If you type text, the program will look for its ASCII encoding. If you type character pairs (e.g., '4D5A'), a HEX search will trigger.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect5_3.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Interactive Side Panel:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect5_4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>All found matches (up to 5000 items) are listed in a convenient side panel. Clicking any address inside this list instantly scrolls the table to the requested row. The panel can be closed with a cross button.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect5_5.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Go To Offset:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect5_6.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>In the 'Edit -&gt; Go to Offset...' menu, type an address in hexadecimal format (e.g., '1C0') and press Enter. The program performs a swift transition.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect6.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>6. DATA INSPECTOR (TYPE INSPECTOR)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect6_1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Decoding Structures:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect6_2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Opening 'File -&gt; File Information' menu brings up the metadata sidebar. When moving the cursor across cells, the inspector reads up to 8 contiguous bytes and instantly converts them into human-readable numeric formats: Binary (1 byte), Int16 Short (2 bytes), Int32 Integer (4 bytes), Int64 Long (8 bytes), and Floating-point Float.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect7.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>7. BOTTOM INFORMATION STATUS BAR</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect7_1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Displays the static file size in bytes with thousand separator formatting. Selecting a single byte shows its exact coordinates in decimal and HEX view, while a mass selection shows 'From .. To' bounds and the exact count of selected bytes.</value>
  </data>
